---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const description =
  'Disclosure and editorial policy for KenAshe.ai: how AI assists the writing, who is accountable, how corrections work, and affiliate or sponsorship disclosures.';
const updated = 'June 25, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Disclosure"
  description={description}
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Disclosure', path: '/disclosure/' },
  ]}
>
  <article class="legal">
    <header class="legal-header">
      <p class="page-mark" aria-hidden="true">// disclosure</p>
      <h1>Disclosure &amp; Editorial Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        This is the most important trust page on the site, so I keep it specific: how content gets
        made, who is accountable, and how I handle money and corrections.
      </p>

      <h2>How content is made</h2>
      <p>
        I build and operate AI systems, and AI assists or fully automates some of the writing and
        building here. In particular, the blog runs as an autonomous system I built: it researches
        current sources, drafts posts, and publishes the ones that clear an automated editorial
        quality gate, under my name as publisher. Posts run under my name without per-post AI
        labels; this page is where the mechanics are stated plainly. Whether a piece is
        AI-assisted or written by hand, I am the publisher and I am accountable for it.
      </p>

      <h2>What I stand behind</h2>
      <p>
        The autonomous system is mine. I monitor it and step in to fix, update, or remove anything
        that does not meet the bar. The durable, firsthand material on this site, such as project
        write-ups, build logs, and tutorials, reflects work I actually did.
      </p>

      <h2>Corrections</h2>
      <p>
        If something here is wrong, tell me at <a href="mailto:hello@kenashe.ai">hello@kenashe.ai</a>
        and I will correct or annotate it. I note meaningful corrections rather than quietly
        changing the record.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate links and sponsorships</h2>
      <p>
        I work in affiliate marketing, so some outbound links on this site may be affiliate links,
        which means I may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. I sometimes receive free or
        discounted access to tools I write about. None of that changes what I choose to cover or
        what I say about it. Where a specific link or post is affiliate or sponsored, it is labeled
        close to the relevant place; this page is the standing policy behind those labels.
      </p>

      <h2>Editorial independence</h2>
      <p>
        My editorial judgment is separate from any commercial relationship. I would rather lose a
        commission than recommend something I do not believe in.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p><a href="mailto:hello@kenashe.ai">hello@kenashe.ai</a></p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .page-mark {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5.5vw, 3.25rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    line-height: 1.02;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
